# Testing Discipline

- Run relevant automated tests after making meaningful code changes.
- If no targeted test exists for changed behavior, add one when it is practical and valuable.
- If existing tests fail because behavior intentionally changed, update those tests to match the new expected behavior.
- Keep tests small and focused on observable behavior.
- Prefer fast, deterministic tests; avoid unnecessary network or timing dependencies.

## Examples

```ts
// Behavior changed: add or update a focused test.
import { expect, test } from "vitest";

test("returns fallback when value is missing", () => {
  expect(getLabel(undefined)).toBe("Unknown");
});
```
